<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idefde9165-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s6211"><num value="6211">§ 6211.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idefde9166-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s6211/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated for each fiscal year such funds as are necessary to carry out this chapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idefde9167-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s6211/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Administrative expenses</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The funds so appropriated shall not be available for payment of the expenses or expenditures of the Board in administering any provisions of an order issued under this chapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idefde9168-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/pl/101/624/tXIX/s1962">Pub. L. 101–624, title XIX, § 1962</ref>, <date date="1990-11-28">Nov. 28, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/3880">104 Stat. 3880</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
